title: Estadio Municipal Nicolás Chahuán Nazar
text: Estadio Municipal Nicolás Chahuán is a multi-use <a href="stadium">stadium</a> in <a href="La%20Calera%2C%20Chile">La Calera</a>, <a href="Valparaiso%20Region">Valparaiso Region</a>, <a href="Chile">Chile</a>. It is currently used mostly for <a href="association%20football">football</a> matches, and is the home ground of <a href="Uni%C3%B3n%20La%20Calera">Unión La Calera</a> of the <a href="Chilean%20Primera%20Divisi%C3%B3n">Chilean Primera División</a>. The stadium was opened in 1950, but it was demolished and completely rebuilt in 2019, with a <a href="seating%20capacity">seating capacity</a> of 9,200 spectators.
